walk on the set with Jimmy Stewart...

464
00:27:42,510 --> 00:27:44,899
... and when l walked on the set,
my knees turned to butter...

465
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:47,630
... and l couldn't remember one word
of what l was supposed to say.

466
00:27:47,790 --> 00:27:51,305
l felt like a little kid just standing there,
just in awe.

467
00:27:51,510 --> 00:27:55,059
l was in New Orleans
a couple of months ago...

468
00:27:55,230 --> 00:28:00,099
... and this is almost 20 years
after the show first aired...

469
00:28:00,270 --> 00:28:02,545
... and l was walking
down Bourbon Street...

470
00:28:02,710 --> 00:28:05,941
... and a guy came up to me
and stopped...

471
00:28:06,110 --> 00:28:09,864
... and looked at me and said,
''General Hazard. ''

472
00:28:10,030 --> 00:28:11,827
And he saluted me.

473
00:28:11,990 --> 00:28:14,458
l was just taken aback.

474
00:28:14,670 --> 00:28:17,230
One of the things
that l'm most proud of...

475
00:28:17,390 --> 00:28:20,268
... l'll tell you, the North and South
is one of my favorites.

476
00:28:20,430 --> 00:28:22,068
There's hours of music.

477
00:28:22,270 --> 00:28:25,262
y ou mean,
which book do l like personally?

478
00:28:25,590 --> 00:28:27,626
My favorite is the middle one,
Love and War...

479
00:28:28,470 --> 00:28:32,827
... because it covers the entire Çivil War,
start to finish.

480
00:28:32,990 --> 00:28:38,826
And l think it's a pretty good
highlight version of the war...

481
00:28:38,990 --> 00:28:41,458
... from the Southern side
as well as the Northern side.

482
00:28:41,670 --> 00:28:44,867
There's no question, number one
was my favorite book, of course it was.

483
00:28:45,070 --> 00:28:47,186
lt broke my heart that l didn't get to--

484
00:28:47,630 --> 00:28:50,224
l didn't get to do this role
and my dad see it.

485
00:28:52,910 --> 00:28:55,868
Anyplace where you find
the essence of civil war...

486
00:28:56,030 --> 00:28:59,227
... where you have one people
divided on an issue...

487
00:28:59,390 --> 00:29:03,144
... makes it a story
that people can relate to...

488
00:29:03,310 --> 00:29:05,870
... no matter where they're from
or what language they speak.

489
00:29:06,070 --> 00:29:09,460
lt was a true...

490
00:29:09,630 --> 00:29:15,865
... extra-rich chocolate piece of life,
you know.

491
00:29:16,030 --> 00:29:17,019
lt truly was.

492
00:29:17,190 --> 00:29:19,909
What l enjoy about the results
is that we're still talking about it...

493
00:29:20,070 --> 00:29:22,664
... and we can still show the film
20 years later.

494
00:29:22,830 --> 00:29:25,264
And we'll still be able to show it
50 years later...

495
00:29:25,430 --> 00:29:27,102
... because it's a story about history.

496
00:29:27,270 --> 00:29:30,865
lt will always be relevant.
lt will always be important.

